Cook the pasta: Heat the broiler to high or the #oven to 500 degrees. Bring a 
large #pot of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Once boiling, add the @Orzo Pasta{6%ounce} 
to the pot and cook for ~{8-9%minutes}, until al dente. Drain and rinse under 
cold water.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, pick the mint leaves of the stems, discarding 
the stems. Thinly slice the mint leaves. Halve the lemon. Peel and halve the 
@Cucumber{1} lengthwise, then scoop out the seeds with a #spoon. Thinly slice the 
cucumber into half moons. Thinly slice the @Garlic{2%clove}. Halve, peel and 
thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Halve, pit, and dice the @Nectarine{1} and 
@Peach{1} into 1-inch cubes.

> A few minutes under the broiler allows juicy peaches and nectarines to develop 
> even more sweetness.

Place the nectarine and peach on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and broil for 
~{4-6%minutes}, until lightly charred.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium 
heat. Add the onion to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until 
softened. Add the garlic to the pan and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes}, until 
fragrant. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Remove the pan from the heat and toss in the orzo, peach, nectarine, cucumber, 
@Feta Cheese{1/4%cup}, a squeeze of @Lemon{1}, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season 
with salt and pepper.

Serve: Divide the orzo salad between #bowls{} and sprinkle with @Mint{1/4%ounce}.

> Refreshing cucumber, mint, and lemon keep this salad feeling fresh and light, 
> while orzo provides a hearty base.